text: Attje Harma Kuiken (born 27 October 1977) is a Dutch politician of the Labour Party (PvdA). Kuiken was born in Groningen and worked at the Ministry of Internal Affairs. She has been an MP since 30 November 2006 (except from January to May 2010). She succeeded Lilianne Ploumen as parliamentary group leader on 22 April 2022. == References == * Bio Parlement.com Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch civil servants Category:Labour Party (Netherlands) politicians Category:Leaders of political parties in the Netherlands Category:Members of the House of Representatives of the Netherlands Category:Politicians from Groningen (city)
